00:21:12,672 --> 00:21:21,278
So, you know, given the advancements in technology, you know, how tough is it?

306
00:21:22,019 --> 00:21:29,585
You know, you're off of photography in the age of digital photos, I mean.

307
00:21:32,935 --> 00:21:34,256
I don't even know how to ask the question.

308
00:21:34,276 --> 00:21:40,340
Well it's pretty easy to make a print that looks a lot like what you want it to, digitally.

309
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:48,285
It may not have the richness of a fine art print made on gelatin silver paper.

310
00:21:49,185 --> 00:21:51,026
But you may not even give a damn about that.

311
00:21:51,126 --> 00:21:55,627
You may just want to see your great aunt, you know, looking good.

312
00:21:57,228 --> 00:22:02,609
But at some point you become, you know, I have a friend that always hated baseball.

313
00:22:03,449 --> 00:22:08,091
And when high def TV came, he could all of a sudden see the spin on the ball from the pitcher.

314
00:22:08,711 --> 00:22:10,572
And it changed it for him completely.

315
00:22:10,932 --> 00:22:14,413
And so when you tune people into the subtleties of what's possible,

316
00:22:15,273 --> 00:22:22,200
all of a sudden they become, it's like listening to your favorite song on an AM radio and then on a good stereo system.

317
00:22:22,981 --> 00:22:25,984
Some people don't care, some people go, whoa.

318
00:22:27,005 --> 00:22:28,947
We want the people to go, whoa.

319
00:22:29,608 --> 00:22:30,829
We've helped set up dark rooms.

320
00:22:32,070 --> 00:22:33,752
People are always reaching out to me.

321
00:22:34,276 --> 00:22:40,303
My dad had a darkroom, it's in the basement, we don't know what to do with it, and we have a list of schools that we have them donated to.

322
00:22:41,365 --> 00:22:44,108
They're usually not worth the kind of money they cost way back when.

323
00:22:45,450 --> 00:22:48,514
But it's better to pass them on than throw them in the junkyard.

324
00:22:49,590 --> 00:22:53,093
Is there a lot of things involved with these old dock rooms?

325
00:22:53,393 --> 00:22:54,434
I'm just curious.

