00:28:07,912 --> 00:28:10,173
We've given many non-photo books to the library.

428
00:28:10,533 --> 00:28:24,033
that's nice what a great library you have oh yes oh man can't say enough good about it yep yep and they did a tremendous job with that library it's it's i don't even call it a library it's a community it is center it's uh they have everything yeah

429
00:28:24,412 --> 00:28:32,717
Well, eventually after I recognized how many duplicate books there were, I convinced Gus that we could probably get rid of some, save some space, make a few bucks.

430
00:28:33,558 --> 00:28:39,261
And in doing so, he and I have both collected books from newer photo book publishers.

431
00:28:40,001 --> 00:28:42,683
And they've become increasingly expensive.

432
00:28:43,243 --> 00:28:45,204
Maybe 10 years ago, you could get a good book for $40, $45.

433
00:28:45,265 --> 00:28:46,405
And now a good book is $65, $70, even $75.

434
00:28:52,509 --> 00:28:55,611
We'd collect them and occasionally we'd get one that was really, really beautiful.

435
00:28:56,612 --> 00:29:01,435
But a lot of the time you'd get it and you might be a little underwhelmed by it and wish you didn't spend the 70 bucks on it.

436
00:29:02,936 --> 00:29:04,617
When I was in school, I was obsessed with it.

437
00:29:04,658 --> 00:29:07,600
I was going to the Mass Art Library all the time and looking at all the books.

438
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:10,842
It was the way to see large bodies of photographs.

439
00:29:11,977 --> 00:29:15,880
When I got out of school, I had to buy them all and I can't really afford that.

440
00:29:16,501 --> 00:29:21,785
I wish that there was somewhere that I could go to just look at them and decide, this one's worth the 70 bucks.

441
00:29:21,805 --> 00:29:22,546
I want to keep that.

442
00:29:22,926 --> 00:29:29,151
So we wanted to offer a place where people could come and look at them and decide if it's worth what it costs.

443
00:29:30,392 --> 00:29:31,513
Or just come and look at them.

