00:30:03,992 --> 00:30:05,632
And you say, well, next month I'll do it.

450
00:30:05,772 --> 00:30:08,593
And they would sell out and they'd be $250.

451
00:30:09,434 --> 00:30:12,455
So we now carry five or six book publishers

452
00:30:13,255 --> 00:30:20,078
we select the best from and so we have a wall of all new books and those are the ones where we have book signings usually and those are exciting.

453
00:30:20,198 --> 00:30:25,160
We did them on Saturdays and nobody came because if it was a nice Saturday who wanted to go to town.

454
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:28,321
We did them on Thursday nights and we had some that were standing room only.

455
00:30:28,481 --> 00:30:31,143
Yes, what a difference just picking the right day.

456
00:30:31,203 --> 00:30:32,183
It's amazing.

457
00:30:32,483 --> 00:30:33,884
Not to do it in July and August.

458
00:30:34,064 --> 00:30:34,204
No.

459
00:30:35,885 --> 00:30:36,566
We learned the hard way.

460
00:30:36,746 --> 00:30:39,308
Yeah, July and August, not much goes on.

461
00:30:40,229 --> 00:30:44,373
A lot of people, vacation time, put it that way.

462
00:30:44,393 --> 00:30:47,436
A lot of us learned that the hard way in July and August.

463
00:30:48,276 --> 00:30:52,140
Alright, so you're brought up about the books and everything else.

464
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:54,102
Are you planning, you know,

