00:31:05,957 --> 00:31:08,557
Or anyone you're excited to bring to Method?

469
00:31:08,997 --> 00:31:10,298
Our last one was two weeks ago.

470
00:31:11,318 --> 00:31:17,019
We won't do another one until the fall, but in the fall, we'll probably have three or four in September and October.

471
00:31:17,779 --> 00:31:19,459
And they'll all be people who've done new books.

472
00:31:20,239 --> 00:31:23,920
We had a wonderful book signing, our last Saturday one, that was somewhat of a success.

473
00:31:24,981 --> 00:31:28,746
A woman who went to MassArt, I think, 30 years ago.

474
00:31:28,846 --> 00:31:33,393
She's done five books about the Basque country, you know, the Spanish part of Spain.

475
00:31:34,314 --> 00:31:35,876
She's a great photographer.

476
00:31:36,697 --> 00:31:40,082
And back in the 70s, I was a fan of punk rock.

477
00:31:41,086 --> 00:31:43,827
And I liked Willie Loco Alexander.

478
00:31:44,567 --> 00:31:46,867
And I like Lou Reed and Velvet Underground.

479
00:31:46,887 --> 00:31:48,448
Lou Reed and the Velvet Underground.

480
00:31:48,468 --> 00:31:49,528
Wow, what memories.

481
00:31:50,188 --> 00:31:52,169
She lives in Gloucester for the last 40 years.

482
00:31:52,209 --> 00:31:57,150
She comes to the opening with a bunch of her very rare books, which we sold a bunch for her.

483
00:31:57,190 --> 00:32:01,531
And her husband of 40 years is Willie Loco Alexander.

484
00:32:01,571 --> 00:32:02,251
No kidding.

485
00:32:02,431 --> 00:32:04,872
Who replaced Lou Reed at the Velvet Underground.

486
00:32:05,872 --> 00:32:07,794
with his hair still spiked up.

487
00:32:07,854 --> 00:32:09,416
He's six foot eight.

488
00:32:10,618 --> 00:32:11,799
And he's funny as hell.

489
00:32:11,899 --> 00:32:12,760
And he was a painter.

490
00:32:13,421 --> 00:32:21,170
And everyone that didn't know them was so surprised that Willie Loco, he's a foot taller than she is.

491
00:32:21,190 --> 00:32:22,531
And he paints wonderfully.

492
00:32:23,993 --> 00:32:33,203
But it's like whoever would have thought that I would get to meet Willy Loco Alexander, and that his wife would be an artist who I respect incredibly.

493
00:32:33,383 --> 00:32:34,104
It's a great thing.

494
00:32:34,204 --> 00:32:36,226
That's Ann Rierich, by the way.

495
00:32:36,306 --> 00:32:38,688
She's incredibly talented, incredibly kind.

496
00:32:39,049 --> 00:32:40,750
You meet her and you feel like you've known her for 20 years.

497
00:32:41,431 --> 00:32:42,592
And she teaches kids.

498
00:32:43,552 --> 00:32:46,593
She teaches at the high school level.

499
00:32:46,974 --> 00:32:53,156
And it's rare that you have someone of that caliber who shows and photographs her in major collections.

500
00:32:53,256 --> 00:32:54,797
That's teaching at that level.

501
00:32:55,317 --> 00:32:55,998
That's a good thing.

502
00:32:56,738 --> 00:32:58,439
So that was a great benefit.

503
00:32:59,059 --> 00:32:59,559
I'm sure.

504
00:32:59,799 --> 00:33:00,680
I like that story.

